.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhavinsoulsbane@thewordsofnagafen>Rhavin Soulsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 874<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/22/03 4:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Rhavin muttered to himself as he tapped out his pipe over a rock near where he sat fishing in the Qeynos Hills. It was clear that he wasn't going to get any relaxing done with all this racket about Stormygale passing through his head. He had known Stormy had been depressed lately, what with her injury and all, but hadn't realized the toll it had taken on her until now. The guild was abuzz about it, and even though he had gone into retirement sometime ago, he was unable to shut out the chatter. He decided that the only way he was going to be able to make it stop was to find Stormy himself.<br>
<br>
After gathering up his gear he began the short walk to Qeynos where he could store his fishing tackle and gather the gear he wore back in his adventuring days. But first, he thought to himself with a bit of a smirk, I will check on my good friend Holly Windstalker...that contemptible shrew of a ranger had given him a fair number of bumps and bruises when he was just a lad growing up in the hills. Now he reviled in killing bears with her around, daring her to stop him.<br>
<br>
As he neared the path from Surefall Glade to Qeynos, lost in thought as he often was, he nearly met his bitter end, to of all things, a horse! He gave the rider a rude gesture and shouted &quot;Watch where you are going ya hippie!&quot; His words trailed off into a mutter when he realized who the rider was. The human druid with hair white as the Everfrost Peaks, and her horse, Doom if he recalled correctly. He also noted that she was somewhat transparent. She was invisible to the naked eye, but not his eyes, enhanced by his familiar they could see her clear as day. But her being invisible in the Hills was troubling. It meant she didn't want to be found and was taking precautions against being seen. He tried following her, but with her horse she easily outpaced him. She seemed to be heading towards the Karana's though.<br>
<br>
He ran the rest of the way to the bank in Qeynos. Once there he deposited his fishing tackle and began to pack up his gear. Everything was packed and readied except he couldn't seem to find his robe. He had passed his Mana Robe on after retiring, but he had kept the robe he had acquired during a visit by The Claw to The Hole to slay the vile Master Yael. The thing had been Loam Encrusted when he got it and it sorely needed....Now remembered where it was, he had left it for the maid to take to the laundry back at the guild house, nearly 3 months ago. Knowing that gnome maid it was probably still dirty as an ogre. He always suspected Merci of getting him a gnomish maid on purpose just to spite him. But now thinking of Merci made him grin. She always had the guild house decorated with odd little smiley faces in all shapes and sizes. He always figured that pipe she smoked and claimed was tabac was really something else entirely. He sighed and muttered &quot;Hippies...&quot;<br>
<br>
He arrived at the guild hall just before nightfall. Upon entering he found the places empty. They were almost surely raiding something tonight. The guild had grown far stronger since he left. And there were many new members that he had never...He finally noticed the walls, no longer were they covered with smiley faces, oh there were a few here and there, but now they were covered with. &quot;White boxes with red X's through them?&quot; he said out load. He didn't know which was more odd this or the smiley faces...No, this was defiantly weirder. Merci was nuts.<br>
<br>
He gave himself a shake and headed off for his apartments. They were just as he had left them, including his robe still slung over a chair and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>still</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> filthy! He cursed Merci over the gnomish maid once more and put on the robe. It may be filthy but it would do. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhavinsoulsbane@thewordsofnagafen>Rhavin Soulsbane</A> at: 7/23/03 12:04 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stormygalewindrunner>Stormygale Windrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 884<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/22/03 5:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> She stretched out her legs and tried to get untangled. She was in a full sweat, even with the mist of the waterfall to cool her. She knew she was coming to an end. This just couldn't go on any longer. She writhed in her bedding, the fire in her spine making her unable to sleep, eat, or drink. She'd drank all the brandy she'd had with her, and now was in agony.  She didn't know if she could move to try an get more.<br>
<br>
She slowly attempted to get untangled from her blanket, but it was useless. She couldn't do it without the world greying out on her from the pain.<br>
Her hands trembled uncontrolably. Probably from lack of drink.  She must be going through withdrawls.<br>
<br>
Finally she gave in, and with her thought going out into the either, she tried to ask her guild for help.  Then she tried to ask Saphron and Athene, but she didn't know if anyone had heard her. &quot;Help me, please....someone....anyone,&quot;<br>
<br>
Her words were garbled with pain and agony.  She couldn't remember if she'd told them where she was or not, but she couldn't try again. It had taken everything out of her to ask.  Her eyes finally rolled up in her head and she gave up and passed out.  <p><b>Stormygale El`Orian</b><img border=0 src="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" /></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stormygalewindrunner>Stormygale Windrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/22/03 5:06 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212128><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zyphindalcohol>Zyphin Dalcohol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 1834<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/22/03 7:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Slowly Zyphin unfolded the map he had so diligently created, pondering over the slim clues that he had aquired.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Let see silk? There are way to many places in this world to get silk, I should know I have hunted most of them.  But the second clue waterfalls should limit it a bunch.&quot;<br>
<br>
Looking over his map he located the waterfalls that he could remember.<br>
<br>
 &quot;The Great Divide has a wonderful waterfall.. Too bad those mindless zombies no longer like me.  Hmm.. there are a few spiders in the mines of Thurgadin.&quot; Zyphin pondered on this for a bit. &quot;I will have to check this one last no need to get the dorfs in a frenzy if  I do not need too.&quot;<br>
<br>
Continuing his search of the map he remembers that spider infested nest in East Karana. &quot;Oh it could not be so simple.&quot;  Tapping the map a few times he figures what the heck and decides to head off to the Karanas to test his luck.  So packing up his meager supplies off he goes in a puff of smoke.<br>
<br>
Arriving at the familiar rings in North Karana, Zyphin notices it is a buzz with young halfings, but decides that his task is too important to mess with the younglings at this time cast Spirit of Eagle and then Improved Superior Camoflage and runs off to the east in search of the goal he hopes to find.<br>
<br>
As he crosses the wooden bridge in to the East Karanas he is stuck by the thought that this place has never seamed so empty.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Ah how I hated this place with all those darn spiders.&quot; Many months had Zyphin hunting these haunts in search of the spider silks that would then be used in his tailoring projects.  <br>
<br>
As he mussed over his past he saw on the horizon the familiar sights of some barbarian fishing huts and in the background the all too familiar sight of a waterfall. The as if a faint whisper he hears in his mind &quot;Help me, please....someone....anyone,&quot; could it be possible that he has found his goal?  Zyphin quickened his pace even at the expense of the fatigue that he was sure would pain him in the morning.<br>
<br>
As he reaches the first hut he sees a figure, obviously in pain, rolling on what he could only believe was a bedroll.  Slowly he approaches and asks<br>
<br>
&quot;Excuse me miss may I be of some service to you?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stormygalewindrunner>Stormygale Windrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 887<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/22/03 7:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> A dream came to her. A runter. Not a bad looking one, and powerful to boot. He smelled of leather. <br>
