<br>
She kept her eyes to the barest of slits as she peeked at him. Pretending to still be out cold. Ah!  She knew this runter! And not only that, he was a guildmate! Oh what to do... what to do. She couldn't hurt a guildmate!<br>
<br>
She considered her options... not many. There was only one thing to do. <br>
<br>
Slowly, acting groggy and bewildered she sat up. Her back flamed and she almost went out again as the world started to grey out around her, but she forced herself back by sheer strength of will. <br>
<br>
&quot;Wha...&quot; she said, then with all her concentration cast her most powerful stun and watched as the force of the wind flopped the runter onto his back, eyes open and unable to move. <br>
<br>
She tried to quickly gather her things, but gave up and grabbed her packs, leaving her bedroll behind. She lept from the hut into the water and almost drowned as she sunk to the bottom. But as she did so, she summoned Doom, and with him under her, she burst from the water at a flat gallop, gasping for air and in so much pain she almost fell off.<br>
<br>
She heard swearing behind her as she ran on, and then she almost ran over someone who screamed &quot;HIPPIE&quot; at her, as she tried to memorized the only spell she could think of, and then paused to cast it. Leaving a swearing runter coming at her at speed, but he was too late. The two second head start and a fast horse was all she needed. <br>
<br>
She landed with a thump, setting off a huge excitement amongst the runters set to watch the hill. But Stormygale was unaware of it.<br>
<br>
Slowly Doom walked on through the woods, trailing a runter or two as he made his way on his own to the only place he knew to go. His mistress was unconscious and out cold.  And he could sense she needed help.<br>
<br>
Stepping as carefully as he could, desperately trying not to jog her or let her slip off, he made his way to the great grand tree in the middle of the wood. He'd been here before many a time and knew his rider concidered this another home. It was closer than her real home, so it would have to do. <br>
<br>
He reached the glade and let loose a mighty neigh. Then stepping carefully to the door he began pounding on it with a shod hoof. <p><b>Stormygale El`Orian</b><img border=0 src="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" /></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stormygalewindrunner>Stormygale Windrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/23/03 1:32 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212128><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhavinsoulsbane@thewordsofnagafen>Rhavin Soulsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 876<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/23/03 12:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> After equipping his robe Rhavin sat and began memorizing the incantations that would take him to the Western Karana's. The last he had seen Stormy she was speeding off that way so that is where his search would begin. Reciting the incantation Rhavin disappeared into a flash of light. Seconds later he found himself on the large grey portal stone in the Western Karana's. And just his luck, it was raining. If there was anything in the world he hated more than Gnomes it was rain.<br>
<br>
Rhavin then quickly cast Abscond and found himself on the Qeynos side of the Karana's. From there he set himself to searching every inn, hut, and guard house, methodically moving back to the east. The Karana's were huge, and it took him nearly an hour to check even the relatively few houses in the area. He then began heading for the gypsies camp in the Northern Karana's. They had been known to give aid to wayward travelers from time to time.<br>
<br>
And then it happened. &quot;Tele mE, pbeyse....sameeny....snyqne,&quot; It was Stormygale. She was in a terrible amount of pain. And drunk too, judging by her slurred speech. She was to the east.<br>
<br>
Rhavin ran, sprinted, his lungs burnt and his side ached but he knew where Stormy was now, she was no longer hiding herself. Crossing the huge wooden bridge into the Eastern Karana's he turned south along the river. As he ran he noticed he was being followed. A pair of gnolls had spotted him and were now trailing him. While they presented no danger to himself he didn't know what condition he would find Stormy in and didn't want to bring them near her. Rhavin turned and quickly cast two spells. After each spell was finished a gnoll erupted in flames as if consumed by the sun.<br>
<br>
Turning to continue after Stormy he had but a second to dive out of the way of an on-coming horse and rider. That was the second time the fool girl had nearly run him down. &quot;@#$@# Hippies&quot; he yelled. Where was that damned girl going now! As he pushed himself to his feet a peck druid sprinted past him after the girl. He quickly fell in behind the peck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=athene>Athene</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/_uimages/ahstarsm.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/23/03 2:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=48>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/eye.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Help me, please....someone....anyone</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
