<br>
“Aye, it may have helped to ease her pain at first, but now it poisons her.  Still, she’ll need to be weaned off it, I think.  Else more a shock to her system.”<br>
<br>
Saphron nodded and began her examination of Stormygale’s body while she still slept fitfully.  There were scratches and bruises in various places.  Whether the result of her journey or the usual falls that a drunk may take was not clear, and Saphron did not suppose it mattered.  She patted the medicine bag Tondar had given her and continued her examination.  Stormygale’s lower back was hot to the touch.  Here there was deep, intense pain.  Saphron pressed her palms flat on Stormygale’s back and recited words of replenishment.  It was a temporary measure to relieve the pain by drawing it out.  The cause of the pain would still have to be addressed.  From her cursory examination, Saphron guessed that the discs of Stormygale’s spine had been torn out of alignment and had healed over but had not been re-aligned.  Thus, the pain had actually gotten more and more intense as she had seemingly recovered.  It was likely that as she had regained strength and attempted to return to her usual routine, sudden, simple movements had caused wrenching pain.  And the drink had probably not helped.  Numbing herself with alcohol, Stormygale had likely increased her tolerance for the pain that should have kept her immobile and seeking a competent healer.  Saphron sighed.  She would get that help now.<br>
<br>
Athene returned from the kitchen where she had gone to fetch hot water and towels as Saphron began to minister to her patient.  Together that cleaned the cuts and abrasions and washed Stormygale as free of the grime that covered her as they could--without waking her or moving her unnecessarily.<br>
<br>
The stew bubbled on the fire, and Athene fetched bowls and utensils from the kitchen for herself and Saphron.  They would try to get Stormygale to eat when she awoke.  <br>
<br>
“We can keep the pain at bay tonight so that she may rest and we can talk to her,” said Saphron.<br>
<br>
Athene nodded and cast the Blessings of Replenishment on the three of them. “It is likely going to be a long night, but let us hope the worst is over.”  <br>
