<br>
&quot;That was very good. Thank you.&quot; she said quietly and sincerely, then with her elbows on the table she put her chin in her still slightly trembling hands, and looked at the two women who were still aprehensively looking back at her. <br>
<br>
&quot;It's alright. I won't bolt again. You can relax.&quot; They didn't seem inclined to, though. Well that was understandable. She'd become very good at eluding these two, and others besides. <br>
<br>
&quot;If you don't mind me asking Stormygale, why are you being so docile? The last time one of us had you, you layed everyone on their backs, flat in the dust.&quot; Athene tried to surpress a giggle as she glanced at Saphron, who had a rather indignant look on her face. <br>
<br>
&quot;Athene, for the first time in almost a year, I am not in screaming pain. I don't know what you've done to stave it off, but you've given me hope. It was more than I could bare anymore,&quot; she covered her eyes as she began to cry. &quot;I just wanted to die, it was so bad.&quot; And she began so sob. Huge racking sobs that left her gasping for breath. &quot;I, I...saw a shaman after the injury... He said my back was broken... and either it would heal or it would not. There was nothing to be done... It got so bad...I just wanted to die,&quot; she sniffled and wiped the tears on the sleeve of her shift.  &quot;I didn't want to be a cripple, a burden on my guild, a burden to my friends. I just wanted to be left alone... to find the courage.... to kill myself, but I could just never quite do it. I kept looking at my locket and my mother's eyes would look at me as if to say, &quot;No daughter. You must not do this thing.&quot; <br>
<br>
She fumbled for her locket and found a nasty surprise. It was gone! <br>
<br>
&quot;Where is it? Where is my locket?! Oh no. It's lost! I've lost it...&quot; and she began to cry again. &quot;My locket... &quot; she laid her head on the table on her crossed arms. &quot;My locket...&quot; she was so tired. She wiped her running nose on the hankie Saphron gave her. Saphron's eyes met Athene's concerned eyes over Stormygale's unknowing head. A message passed between them. <br>
<br>
Saphron went into the kitchen and came out with another glass of water.  &quot;Here Stormy, drink. It will calm you.&quot; <br>
<br>
Her hands still trembling some, she took the water and drank. Then Saphron and Athene gently helped her back to her place by the fire and watched as the drugged water took effect and Stormygale fell asleep, still mumbling about her locket. <br>
<br>
&quot;You were right Athene,&quot; Saphron said quietly. &quot;There is more than just physical pain here.&quot; We have much to do. <br>
<br>
Athene, looking down with pity shining in her eyes and replied &quot;Yes. We'd best be careful though. One wrong step and she'll suicide.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Then we'll just have to do it right, eh?&quot; Saphron winked and her friend and they smiled. <br>
<br>
