<br>
&quot;I'll watch her, Athene. Get some rest.&quot;<br>
<br>
They would worry about the locket later. For now, Saphron wanted to get a good look at Stormy's back. And now, while she was asleep, was the best time.<br>
<br>
Saphron was all business as she examined Stormygale's back. Laying both hands on the bare flesh, she winced in pain as her clerical senses fused with Stormygale's. She concentrated deeper, trying to feel the pain with Stormygale, trying to sense the exact origin of the inflammation. As she moved her sensitive fingers over the maligned disc, Saphron grimaced terribly and fell to her knees, the wind knocked out of her completely.<br>
<br>
&quot;Whatsa matter, Runter?&quot; Stormygale chided softly, &quot;Too much for ya?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Go back to sleep, whelp, &quot;Saphron flashed Stormygale a knowing smile and, getting to her feet, reached for the medicine bag that Tondar had given her, &quot;That's the second time this week you've knocked me down.&quot;<br>
<br>
The two women, once bitter rivals, shared a short lived smile. <br>
<br>
&quot;Stormygale, I don't know how you've been conscious through this pain, let alone riding and running. You are truly a remarkable girl.&quot;<br>
<br>
Saphron looked her friend squarely in the eyes. <br>
<br>
&quot;And, I've missed you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Saphron?&quot; Stormygale inquired, &quot;Where is your guild badge?&quot;<br>
<br>
The cleric spoke quietly as she diligently prepared the medicine pack, &quot;I've left the Knights, Stormy. You know? I've felt so empty inside of late, and I think I am starting to realize why. I thought that with you joining the Claw, and with Athene doing that whole marriage thing and joining the Ring of Valor, and the others doing who knows what . . . well, I felt that I needed to find a new home quickly as well. Well, HOGWASH!&quot;<br>
<br>
Stormygale snickered in spite of the pain.<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't get me wrong, Girl, they were good people and a good guild, but they just weren't . . . family.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now, this might burn a bit. I'm no expert with shamanistic medicine.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;GAH!&quot; Stormygale cried out as the medicine bag was placed on her lower back.<br>
<br>
&quot;OK, it's really gonna hurt,&quot; Saphron smiled at Stormy, &quot;But it's going to help. Tondar promised.&quot;<br>
<br>
The warm, wet pack on Stormygale's back began to smoulder and glow with healing properties. Shamen really were amazing.<br>
<br>
Saphron began to massage the area around the pack, as Tondar had explained, and she felt bones cracking beneath her fingers. There was no response from Stormygale, who was apparently too concerned with the burning sensation to realize her muscles were being manipulated so that her bones were being realigned.<br>
<br>
&quot;What are you doing back there? Barbecuing me?!?&quot; Stormygale hissed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Stormy, I have no idea how, but I think this is working.&quot; <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:gold;font-family:Garamond;font-size:medium;">Saphron LaFeete</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;font-family:garamond;font-size:small;">High Priestess of Bristlebane </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saphronlafeete>Saphron LaFeete</A> at: 7/24/03 11:10 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stormygalewindrunner>Stormygale Windrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 899<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/24/03 11:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> &quot;You know what, my friend? I think you're right.&quot; Stormygale gasped slowly, trying to remember to breathe. But the pain was no worse than the what she'd originally experienced, and had endured this last year so she could bear it. <br>
<br>
&quot;If your so dumb to join a guild who dosen't love you, then you deserve what you get.&quot; Stormgale bit off a yell as Saphron gave her a pinch. &quot;Ok ok. I'll shut up. But you should have joined The Claw of Nagafen with me. You and you too, Athene. It's like Natural Selection was, only better.&quot; Stormygale let out a yelp. &quot;Quit pinching me woman, or I'll blow you off your feet again!&quot; She clenched her teeth as the burning continued. <br>
<br>
&quot;But I'm serious. Join Quaras and me in The Claw. Better people you will not find. They are my family now, and I love them. Just consider it, ok?&quot; Stormygale believed they would love the Claw of Nagafen, and the talking helped keep her mind off the growing waves of fire in her back.<br>
<br>
Athene suddenly asked, &quot;What are they like?&quot; And Stormygale smiled to herself. She heard the real interest. She'd known these women for years upon years and could almost read their thoughts at will. <br>
<br>
&quot;They are honorable people, generous and kind. If you are accepted, you are family. It is not easy to garner entrance as they are very cautious who they allow into their hearts and home. But I love them, and they love me. Else they would not have hunted me also. Tell me, would either of your old guilds have cared so much for you?&quot; <br>
<br>
Stormygale watched them ponder that question and come up blank.  She had them. They just didn't know it yet. heh. <br>
<br>
God her back burned. She did not believe much in her Icy God, Tunare, but she sent a little prayer out to her anyway. Maybe at least she could cool the fire a bit?  <p><b>Stormygale El`Orian</b><img border=0 src="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" /></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stormygalewindrunner>Stormygale Windrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/24/03 11:37 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212128><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=athene>Athene</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/_uimages/ahstarsm.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/24/03 11:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=59>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/eye.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> At that moment, there came a light rap on the door.  Athene made eye contact with Saphron and stood.  “I’ll see what that is about.”  She smoothed her hair down, running her hands down the single braid of hair.  She’d been up all night.  She figured she must look a bit haggard.<br>
<br>
She crossed quickly to the door and opened it.  On the threshold a lovely wood-elf druid stood.  She was well-dressed and wore the insignia of The Claw of Nagafen, Stormygale’s guild.  <br>
<br>
“Please enter,” Athene said.  “I think the one you seek is here.”  She stepped back and made a wide motion with her arm toward the large open room.  “Welcome to the guild hall of Natural Selection.  It’s really more of a retreat now, but it was my home for a long while and you are welcome.  My name is Athene.”  <br>
<br>
The young woman—a druid judging from her armor and the Nature Walker’s scimitar she carried—stepped in confidently.  She had never been down the paths that had taken her here; and now, knowing that she had found her quarry, she was intensely curious about this place.  “I’m Kalyndria of the Claw of Nagafen.  Thank you.  How is Stormygale?”<br>
<br>
“Come in, and see for yourself.  She’s much the worse for wear and pain.  Saphron is tending to her.  She’s a cleric.”<br>
<br>
Kalyndria brighted.  “Yes, I know Saphron.  We came here together—sort of.  I lost sight of her.  Fast pony.”<br>
<br>
Together the two women walked toward the fire where Saphron still hovered over Stormygale.<br>
<br>
Athene was greatly relieved.  Her own application to the Claw was completed and stowed in her bags.  That Stormygale had, herself, suggested that the two women apply, was the most fortuitous circumstance they could have imagined.  <br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=athene>Athene</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/_uimages/ahstarsm.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/24/03 11:48 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stormygalewindrunner>Stormygale Windrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 900<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/24/03 12:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> &quot;Kaly!&quot; Stormygale breathed with a smile. &quot;It is good to see you my friend! Do you see these two women who torture me? These are my friends, Athene and Saphron.  We used to be guildmates.  Athene, Saphron, this is my guildmate, Kalyndria. I'm trying to convince these two old friends to join The Claw. If nothing else, they'd work well in the torture chambers!&quot; she yelped as Saphron pinched her again.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tell them how great CoN is, Kaly, while Saphron continues to burn the skin off my back....&quot;<br>
<br>
